<h2 id="workiz-plans-breakdown">Workiz Plans Breakdown</h2>

<div class="prose max-w-none">
<p>Each Workiz plan targets different HVAC company sizes. Here's what you get and who should choose each plan:</p>

<h3>Basic Plan ($49/month)</h3>
<p>Best for solo HVAC contractors or husband-wife teams. Includes scheduling, invoicing, customer management, and mobile app. Limited to 2 users and 1,000 customers. Missing advanced reporting, custom forms, and multi-location support.</p>

<p>Real-world cost for HVAC contractors: $49-87/month (if you add payment processing on $3,000 monthly revenue, that's $87 in processing fees alone).</p>

<h3>Professional Plan ($99/month)</h3>
<p>The sweet spot for 3-8 person HVAC teams. Adds advanced reporting, custom estimates, QuickBooks integration, and up to 5,000 customers. Supports recurring service agreements, which are crucial for maintenance contracts.</p>

<p>Typical HVAC company cost: $150-250/month including extra users and processing fees. This plan handles $500K-2M annual revenue comfortably.</p>

<h3>Premium Plan ($199/month)</h3>
<p>Built for larger HVAC operations with 8-20 technicians. Includes multi-location support, advanced inventory tracking, custom user roles, and unlimited customers. Essential features for companies running separate commercial and residential divisions.</p>

<p>Real HVAC company cost: $300-500/month. Companies at this level typically process $50K-100K monthly through the system, adding $1,450-2,900 in processing fees.</p>
</div>

