<p><strong><a href="https://get.toggl.com/f71dwhbrzvzz" rel="sponsored nofollow">Toggl Track</a> for Time Tracking:</strong> Workiz's built-in time tracking is basic. Toggl provides detailed labor cost analysis and project profitability tracking. $9-18 per user monthly, but helps HVAC companies identify which services are actually profitable.</p>

<p><strong><a href="https://get.apollo.io/fxnpnadnv4lb" rel="sponsored nofollow">Apollo.io</a> for Lead Generation:</strong> Workiz handles existing customers well but lacks prospecting tools. Apollo helps HVAC companies find commercial prospects and build maintenance contract pipelines. Starts at $49/month for prospecting tools that can generate $10K-50K in new monthly recurring revenue.</p>

<p><strong>QuickBooks Integration:</strong> Essential for HVAC companies with complex job costing. Workiz's native accounting is limited. QuickBooks integration costs $29/month extra but provides real job profitability tracking and better financial reporting.</p>

<p>These tools typically add $100-200 monthly to your software stack but provide measurable ROI through better efficiency and lead generation.</p>
</div>

