<h2 id="bottom-line">Bottom Line for HVAC Companies</h2>

<div class="prose max-w-none">
<p>Workiz pricing works best for HVAC companies that:</p>
<ul>
<li>Process high transaction volumes (makes the 2.9% fee worthwhile vs flat monthly fees)</li>
<li>Need strong inventory management and custom forms</li>
<li>Have teams of 5-15 users (sweet spot for per-user pricing)</li>
<li>Focus on commercial work requiring detailed documentation</li>
</ul>

<p>Skip Workiz if you:</p>
<ul>
<li>Have large teams (20+ users make per-user costs expensive)</li>
<li>Process low monthly payment volumes (flat-rate competitors are cheaper)</li>
<li>Need advanced HVAC-specific features like load calculations</li>
<li>Want unlimited users for seasonal flexibility</li>
</ul>

<p>Alternative recommendations:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Small teams (1-5 users):</strong> <a href="https://housecallpro.partnerlinks.io/auy5xcz257sw" rel="sponsored nofollow">Housecall Pro</a> offers better value at $149/month for unlimited users</li>
<li><strong>Large teams (15+ users):</strong> <a href="https://go.getjobber.com/bo42cjptz4m2" rel="sponsored nofollow">Jobber</a> at $169/month with unlimited users</li>
<li><strong>Enterprise HVAC:</strong> <a href="/hvac/crm/servicetitan-alternatives">ServiceTitan alternatives</a> provide more advanced HVAC features</li>
</ul>

<p>Budget realistically for total Workiz costs: plan price + extra users + 3% of processed payments + $50-100 monthly in SMS/integration fees. For most HVAC companies, this totals $200-500 monthly depending on size and transaction volume.</p>

